OL,3,CFather who carries disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs waiting seven months for
OL,5,Csuitable home
OL,7,F"And then on that bed there is where
OL,8,Fme and Harry sleep. There's five of us
OL,9,Fin one room."
OL,11,FDespite Stephen searching every night
OL,12,Fon his Housing Association's property
OL,13,Fpool, he's yet to find anywhere with
OL,14,Fenough room.
OL,16,FHe said: "I don't feel like I'm
OL,17,Fgetting any support. I had to take my
OL,18,Fchildren away from the situation they
OL,19,Fwere in to give them a better life,
OL,20,Fbut I feel like they've gone backwards.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
