OL,3,CFather who carries disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs waiting seven months for
OL,5,Csuitable home
OL,7,F"They're frozen in time because
OL,8,Fthere's so much they should be getting
OL,9,Fbut they're not. There's no light at
OL,10,Fthe end of the tunnel, it's just
OL,11,Fgetting dimmer and dimmer."
OL,13,FThe lack of space makes it impossible
OL,14,Ffor Stephen's seven-year-old son
OL,15,FHarry, who has cerebral palsy, to use
OL,16,Fhis wheelchair or mobility aids to
OL,17,Fmove around the house - which could
OL,18,Fhave a lifelong impact on his mobility.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
