OL,3,CFather who carries disabled son up
OL,4,Cstairs waiting seven months for
OL,5,Csuitable home
OL,7,FMost people with cerebral palsy have
OL,8,Fmobility issues, but regular exercise
OL,9,Fand play are crucial for maintaining
OL,10,Fand improving their physical strength.
OL,12,FStephen said: "The physio said it's...
OL,13,Fgetting worse and it could get to a
OL,14,Fpoint where he won't be able to
OL,15,Fstretch his legs out.
OL,17,F"He gets in the bath, but he's
OL,18,Fbruising his legs. A wet room he'd be
OL,19,Fin his wheelchair and have a proper
OL,20,Fshower. It'd be so much easier."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
